  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-03-09",
    "date": "2021-04-15T21:38:35Z",
    "text": "Inventor Diversity for Economic Advancement Act of 2021 or the IDEA Act\n\nThis bill requires the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) to request\u00a0demographic information from the inventor on each patent application submitted to the USPTO.\n\nInventors shall not be required to provide the requested information, which shall include gender, race, and military or veteran status.\n\nThe USPTO shall (1) publish an annual public report about the collected data, including the collected data broken down by the types of technology covered by the patent applications; and (2) make the underlying data publicly available."
  },
